im Fashion contextualizes modest wardrobe styling within Islamic and global consumer cultures, interviewing key players including designers, bloggers, shoppers, store clerks, and shop owners. Focusing on Britain, North America, and Turkey, Lewis provides insights into the ways young Muslim women use multiple fashion systems to negotiate religion, identity, and ethnicity.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aFashionxGreat Britain. 0aFashionxNorth America. 0aFashionxTurkey. 0aFashionzGreat Britain. 0aFashionzNorth America. 0aFashionzTurkey. 0aMuslim womenxClothingxGreat Britain. 0aMuslim womenxClothingxNorth America. 0aMuslim womenxClothingxTurkey. 0aMuslim womenxClothingzGreat Britain. 0aMuslim womenxClothingzNorth America. 0aMuslim womenxClothingzTurkey. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071182040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822375340zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822375340423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822375340.jpg  a978-3-11-071182-0  DUK eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles